This is caused by a limitation in the wiki markup language / renderer described at CONF-2494 and cannot be fixed without breaking backwards compatibility.

h4. Workaround

Insert the html escape sequence for the backslash character as:

{code}
&#92;
{code}
{panel}

If I include a path whose subfolder leads with an underscore, the preceding backlash won't appear.  The examples below should contain the same text, but the backslash is being dropped:

{code}example\_subfolder{code}

example\_subfolder

