It would be quite handy if one could set JIRA's initial banner with a {{-Datlassian.jira.banner=...}} system property.

Typically one has a production JIRA, and a staging JIRA whose data is periodically synced from production. It is a good idea to have a banner on the Staging JIRA, so users don't mistake it for production. Yet because data is regularly synced, any hand-set banner would be lost. Wouldn't it be nice if, in Staging JIRA's {{bin/setenv.sh}}, you could set 

{noformat}JVM_EXTRA_ARGS="-Datlassian.jira.banner=<h2>This is staging, last refreshed at `date`. Any changes will be lost</h2>"{noformat}

