The documentation [Migrating JIRA to Another Server|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA044/Migrating+JIRA+to+Another+Server] is also used for upgrading JIRA from version prior to 4.0. 

There is a step about Home directory:
{noformat}
2.3 Back up your JIRA Home directory
Ensure JIRA is shut down before continuing.

The location of this directory is defined within the jira-application.properties configuration file, which is located inside the <jira-application-dir>/WEB-INF/classes directory within your JIRA Installation Directory.
{noformat}
However, prior to JIRA 4.0, there is no Home Directory. This step should be skipped for an upgrade from JIRA prior to 4.0.

